BUG: Tap destination pattern `* -> target` matches ALL flows

The tap pattern `~tap(* -> target)` should only fire when an event
transitions TO `target`. Currently it fires for ALL flows, including
flows that never call `target`.

Example:
  ~tap(* -> target)
  | Transition _ |> log()

  ~target()      // tap SHOULD fire (calls target)
  | done _ |> _

  ~other()       // tap should NOT fire (doesn't call target)
  | done _ |> _

Current behavior: tap fires for BOTH flows (and koru:start/end)
Expected behavior: tap fires ONLY for the flow that calls target

Root cause: The tap transform in taps.kz isn't correctly filtering
by destination pattern - it's applying to all flows.

Acceptance criteria:
- ~tap(* -> X) only fires for flows that actually call X
- ~tap(* -> X) does NOT fire for flows that call other events
- koru:start and koru:end should never match destination patterns
- metatype_binding step should always be generated before tap handler
